ast.name: hawaii store
ast.comment:
A library that provide cloud-based key-value storage.
The library requires an account with Microsoft Research Project Hawaii Services. See demo for usage example.

DuVNbhO7chz14HpnvYHqGqFR.text: The Project Hawaii Key Store service provides a simple key-value storage in the cloud. This is useful to build simple app that share data across devices.

M4nQzOFSgk2IEtTCtYGG5Oe6.text: In order to use the Project Hawaii services, you will need to request an Application ID.

H5hw4s4D7sDEgAzhOkeRt0F2.text: For the purpose of this example, we send the user to the Project Hawaii home page so that he can copy the AppId in the clipboard.

sHxYepC1seJBjpY9qbdYsfJb.text: Now, we let the user paste the AppId in the text box.

FEvnRTYo4Dh3VAcsDVDQt2rb.text: Call the `initialize` action once with your AppId before calling any other action.

MBO0wGg72F400iaJjFccCC0S.text: The library acts as a simple key-value store of strings. Simply call the `set at` action with the key and value.
The library acts as a simple key-value store of strings. Simply call the `set at` action with the key and value; `set at` returns a value indicating if it was successful.

DuVNbhO7chz14HpnvYHqGqFR.text: The Project Hawaii Key Store service provides a simple key-value storage in the cloud. This is useful to build simple app that share data across devices. Note that this library does not work offline and requires the user to be connected to internet.

SGcftKfQFW7hVSiURtiBp2Tz.text: Simply call  the `at` action with the key to retrieve.

P62MlMdZYx3124CC1AYHH4Av.text: If the key does not exist in the store, it will return an invalid string. Therefore, make sure to test if the value is invalid before using it.

LQ6vNYYxDftvysTOhF08fuQJ.text: You can retrieve a filtered list of key-value pairs using `select`. The "magic" argument is the prefix of the desired key.
